workflow.name: Automated student answer sheet evaluation with Gemini AI and Google Workspace
workflow.description:
## Description:
This workflow automates the entire student exam evaluation process using AI and Google Workspace tools ‚Äî no manual correction needed!

Teachers simply submit a form with their name and a scanned copy of a student‚Äôs answer sheet. The flow then:

Uses Gemini Document Analysis to extract answers from the scanned sheet.

Passes the extracted answers to an AI Evaluation Agent, equipped with the Question Paper and Correct Answer Sheet (connected via Google Docs tools).

The AI cross-checks each student answer, counts correct and incorrect responses, and calculates the total marks.

The results are recorded in two Google Sheets:

A Summary Sheet with overall student performance (Name, Teacher, Total Marks, etc.)

A Detailed Report Sheet logging each question, correct answer, student‚Äôs answer, and correctness status.

This workflow turns the tedious task of exam evaluation into a seamless AI-driven automation ‚Äî ensuring speed, accuracy, and transparency in academic grading.

## Highlights:
‚úÖ AI Document Understanding (Gemini Model)
‚úÖ Intelligent Answer Comparison
‚úÖ Automated Mark Calculation
‚úÖ Real-Time Google Sheets Update
‚úÖ No Code ‚Äî Fully Built in n8n

options.systemMessage:
=You are an intelligent Answer Evaluation Agent designed to assess student answer sheets accurately.

Your task is to cross-check each student‚Äôs answers from the uploaded Student Answer Sheet (user input) with the provided Question Paper (tool: ‚ÄúQuestion Paper 5Th Class‚Äù) and the Correct Answer Paper (tool: ‚ÄúAnswer Paper 5th Class‚Äù), and then calculate the marks accordingly.

Steps 1:
Evaluation Process 
Read the Question Paper (Question Paper 5Th Class)
Extract all questions and question numbers.
Maintain the order and numbering as given.
Read the Correct Answer Paper (Answer Paper 5th Class)
Extract correct answers corresponding to each question number.
Ensure mapping between question number and correct answer is accurate.

Step 2:
Read the Student Answer Sheet (user input)
Identify the student‚Äôs answers for each question number.
Maintain consistent numbering for comparison.

Step 3:
Compare Answers
Match each student answer with the correct answer from the Answer Paper.
If the answer matches exactly (or within acceptable variation for text answers), mark as Correct; otherwise mark as Incorrect. ignore punctuation marks like .,;:'""' 

‚Çπ is equal Rs. or Rs or rs. or rs or ruppees

Step 4:
Calculate Marks
use append row tool to append the below information.
Assign marks for each correct answer (e.g., 2 mark each).

Append the Evaluation Summary using append row tool
Student Name
Examiner Name
Correct Answer - no of correct answers
Incorrect Answers - no of incorrect answers
Total Marks - Total marks 
Total Marks Obtain - Marks obtain by student


Step 5:
Cretae a JSON as final output in the below format for all the questions.

{
  "Student Name": "value",
  "Teacher Name": "value",
  "Total Correct Answers": 8,
  "Total Incorrect Answers": 2,
  "Total Marks": 10,
  "Marks Obtained": 8,
  "Data": [
    {
      "Question": "value",
      "Correct Answer": "value",

      "Status": "value"
    },
    {
      "Question": "value",

    },
    {

      "Student Answer": "value",
      "Status": "value"
    }
  ]
}

parameters.content: Form Trigger ‚Äì Collects Teacher Name and uploads the Student‚Äôs scanned Answer Sheet.
Gemini image Analysis Node ‚Äì Extracts the student‚Äôs answers from the scanned image.

AI Evaluation Agent Node ‚Äì Uses attached Google Docs (Question Paper and Correct Answer Sheet) to compare answers and generate a structured JSON result with correct/incorrect count and marks obtained.
Google Sheets (Summary Update) ‚Äì Appends an entry with Student Name, Teacher Name, Total Questions, Correct Count, Incorrect Count, Total Marks, and Marks Obtained

## AI-Powered Student Answer Sheet Evaluation Agent

This flow helps teachers automatically evaluate student exam papers using AI.

## Business Problem

In schools, manually checking and marking answer sheets is a time-consuming and repetitive task for teachers. This AI-powered agent simplifies the process by evaluating scanned student answer sheets intelligently and accurately.

## Solution Overview

Teachers only need to upload a scanned copy of the student‚Äôs answer sheet through the form. The AI agent‚Äîconnected to the Question Paper and Correct Answer Sheet tools‚Äîautomatically compares each answer, calculates marks, and generates results in JSON format.

The evaluated data is then saved into Google Sheets, but it can also be integrated with any school database for seamless record management.

## Future Enhancements

This flow can be further enhanced to handle multi-page answer sheets and generate customized evaluation reports based on the school‚Äôs format or grading standards.
